post_summaries.description: The image is a close-up shot of a woman smiling at the camera. She's holding a large cone filled with french fries covered in ketchup. She is wearing a black hoodie with the words "LORD OF THE FRIES" printed in white and red. The background is blurred, suggesting an outdoor setting.

The Instagram post is from "chief_meta_chicks" featuring Amanda Leigh Walker, an entrepreneur, business coach, and founder of "Lord of the Fries". The post includes a quote emphasizing building a sustainable and supportive business. It also promotes upcoming events and holistic approaches to business.

The image is an Instagram post by amanda.leigh.walker promoting her workshop submission to SXSW Sydney 2025. The workshop is titled "Human Design for Visionary Leaders: The Energetic Edge of the Future" and focuses on using Human Design as a tool for leadership.

The image is an Instagram post by amanda.leigh.walker promoting her pitch for a SXSW Sydney talk on sustainability as the key to business success. She emphasizes a holistic approach to sustainability beyond just eco-friendly products, focusing on internal alignment and personal wellbeing. She is the founder of Lord of the Fries and a life coach and business mentor.
The image shows a video still of a field with sheep in Lily Dale, New York. The post describes a spiritual experience the poster had in Lily Dale, involving mediums and spirit connections.

The image is a screenshot of an Instagram post by amanda.leigh.walker. The post is a video where she recommends taking yourself out on a date. The video shows Amanda smiling and talking about taking herself to the country to a lotus farm. The caption includes hashtags like #dateyourself, #forestbathing, #selfcaretips, and #vegan.
